President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Coleen S. Kalina as the Executive Director of the Intelligence Oversight Board. Kalina is a twenty-eight-year veteran of the Intelligence Community and has held notable leadership positions in the Defense Intelligence Agency, Office of the Director of National Intelligence, and National Security Council. Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Michele Kessler and Phyllis J. Washington as Members of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts.